  
                    
                        
                
                
            Southampton have named former RB Leipzig boss Ralph Hasenhuttl as their new manager on a two-and-a-half year deal.The Saints sacked Mark Hughes on Monday, eight months after taking charge, with the club 18th in the Premier League table.Austrian Hasenhuttl, 51, has been out of work since leaving Leipzig in May, ending a two-year spell at the club.
    
        
More to follow.
 
